The only thing RStudio asks me to do is to reload the visual editor when I change the output format.

00:11:23.179 --> 00:11:29.979
And let's go ahead and render that as well. And here we go. Our document title is now a title

00:11:29.979 --> 00:11:36.859
slide. I can actually scroll through the different slides that I have. Each of them are sort of

00:11:36.859 --> 00:11:43.979
determined by these headings. Um, so let's go ahead and actually turn this into a slightly

00:11:43.979 --> 00:11:50.539
more reasonable slide deck. Now things worked, but my text is a little bit squished. Um, I am going

00:11:50.539 --> 00:11:59.979
to take a look at the, um, outline, um, view here where I can see the different sections in my document.

00:12:03.500 --> 00:12:10.380
Um, and I'm going to make these my, uh, second level headings. So these, uh, particular data

00:12:10.380 --> 00:12:15.739
species and penguins are going to be second level headings. And let's go ahead and insert some first

00:12:15.739 --> 00:12:21.580
level headings as well. Using the insert anything tool, we'll say that I want a first level heading.

00:12:22.219 --> 00:12:31.020
Maybe first I want something like introduction. And then at the end, I might want something like, um,

00:12:31.260 --> 00:12:40.619
um, analysis and maybe a slide here, something like modeling results.

00:12:43.260 --> 00:12:49.979
And then I might finally want another slide, um, at the end called references. Remember those

